## Data Sources for sensor_group_segment

### 1. Temperature Data вҖ” ETL via `temperature_data_export_package`

ETL is handled by `temperature_data_export_package` (read-only, from `beehero-streamlit-app`).
Functions used: `load_sensor_samples()`, `load_gateway_samples()`, `add_hive_size_bucket()`.

Local samples are stored under `data/samples/group_{id}/{date}/` as Parquet files.

#### Sensor samples (`{id}_{date}_sensor_temperature.parquet`)

| Column | Type | Description |
|--------|------|-------------|
| `sensor_mac_address` | string | Hive sensor identifier |
| `timestamp` | datetime | 30-minute bin (resampled mean) |
| `pcb_temperature_one` | float | **Hive** internal temperature (В°C) |
| `gateway_mac_address` | string | Gateway the sensor reported through |
| `group_id` | string | Hive group |
| `hive_size_bucket` | string | `'small'` / `'medium'` / `'large'` вҖ” derived from bee_frames |

#### Gateway samples (`{id}_{date}_gateway_temperature.parquet`)

| Column | Type | Description |
|--------|------|-------------|
| `gateway_mac_address` | string | Gateway device |
| `timestamp` | datetime | Measurement timestamp |
| `pcb_temperature_two` | float | **Ambient** (outdoor) temperature (В°C) |

#### Hive updates (`{id}_{date}_hive_updates.parquet`)

| Column | Type | Description |
|--------|------|-------------|
| `sensor_mac_address` | string | Hive sensor |
| `created` | datetime | When the update was recorded |
| `group_id` | string | Hive group |
| `bee_frames` | int | bee frame count |
| `model` | string | Model version used for this date |

